{"title":"Scarab Carbon Seat Mast Makes Steel More Comfy, Plus New Andes Road Touring Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/scarab-carbon-seat-mast-makes-steel-more-comfy-plus-new-andes-road-touring-bike/","date":1724708996000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"(Photo by Will Bender/Scarab)\" /></p>\n<p>The Colombian framebuilders at Scarab Cycles had a number of interesting bits of news to share at MADE, probably most interesting being their first-ever addition of carbon to classic steel construction. Dubbed, the Composite Damping System, Scarab extends a carbon seattube from the BB up and out as a seatmast, boosting rider comfort and shedding grams from their road, all-road, and gravel frames. Plus, they’ve also added a new Andes road touring bike model built for the longest Brevet-style events…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Scarab Composite Damping System steel &amp; carbon comfort</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Santa Rosa Integrated steel road bike with new Composite Damping System carbon seatmast, up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_up-close-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo by Will Bender/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Scarab frames until now have been exclusively made of steel. But their new Composite Damping System shakes things up, offering the alternative of a carbon fiber tube replacing the bulk of a bike’s seattube and a good portion of the seatpost.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The direct reasoning is to improve rider comfort with the carbon tube better suited to damp high-frequency vibrations. But a more modern look and presumably a little weight savings deliver added side benefits.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2400\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Santa Rosa Integrated steel road bike with new Composite Damping System carbon seatmast, carbon fiber tube details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details.jpg 2400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details-297x149.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details-1536x768.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details-768x384.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_carbon-tube-details-2048x1024.jpg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo by Will Bender/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>What remains steel is a small seattube stub that extends up from the bottom bracket joint to mount a front derailleur on 2x bike frames, another short section at the seat cluster where the seatstays and toptube meet, and on top a steel seatmast head. In between, they bond a carbon tube into the steel frame, extending up as a seatmast to meet the new head, and maintain height adjustability.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Santa Rosa Integrated steel road bike with new Composite Damping System carbon seatmast\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_CDS-seat-mast-detail-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo by Will Bender/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Scarab <a href=\"http://scarabcycles.com/en-us/pages/carbon-damping-system\" target=\"_blank\">Composite Damping System</a> is now available as an extra $800 add-on option on their Santa Rosa road, Apuna all-road, and Paramo gravel bikes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, up close\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_frameset-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Technically an addition to Scarab’s all-road bike family, they built the Andes for ultra-distance ride comfort and durability. It was born out of a development collaboration with Ronnie Garcia of Scarab’s Brooklyn, NY boutique partner Eighth Hour Bike Studio. “<em>Garcia’s expertise and creative approach helped shape our vision of what our brevet bike should be</em>”, says Scarab.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Scarab crafts the brevet road touring frame &amp; fork from a mix of premium butted steel tubes for a smooth ride that can still handle plenty of abuse, using more classically-sized and thicker main tubes vs. the oversize that dominates most modern steel bikes. Angel Bicycles – a framebuilder near Scarab in El Retiro, Colombia – builds its custom steel fork.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Andes is designed to sport full-coverage fenders, dynamo powered-lights lightweight touring racks &amp; bags, and to be ridden far. Optimal tires with fenders are 700c x 32-35mm, while max tire clearance without is 42mm. But you can also run 650b wheels up to 48mm wide, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, fork detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor_custom-Angel-steel-fork-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It features completely external cable routing but internal dynamo wiring routing, a braze-on front derailleur mount, complete rack &amp; fender mounts, 12mm thru-axles, post mount disc brakes, a threaded BB, 1 1/8” external headset, and a replaceable alloy rear derailleur hanger.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, painted-to-match\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_Condor-watercolor-painted-to-match-accessories-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The custom Scarab <a href=\"http://scarabcycles.com/en-us/products/andes\" target=\"_blank\">Andes</a> frameset starts at $4000 on its own. Then you can add on things like custom paint, custom steel racks, and painted-to-match components or accessories.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>New Condor watercolor paint scheme</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, new Condor watercolor paint finish toptube detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-toptube-detail-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This new complete Andes brevet bike build also played the blank canvas for Scarab’s new Condor watercolor paint scheme.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, new Condor watercolor paint job detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paintjob-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>The Condor Paint Scheme is a tribute to the majesty and freedom of the Andean condor. The water-color-like design is a collaboration between local artist “Washedog” and Alejandro Bustamante, Scarab’s creative director, and paint lead. The final work features a unique mix of techniques, including watercolor, transfer, paintbrush, and traditional stencil, giving the design a depth that reflects Scarab’s strong attachment to the Andean mountains.”</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles all-new Andes brevet road touring bike, new Condor watercolor paint scheme\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Cycles-Andes-brevet-steel-endurance-road-touring-bike_new-Condor-watercolor-paint-scheme-detail-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Condor aesthetic concept is said to expand far beyond the bike, and Scarab will offer ‘off-bike’ items like jerseys, t-shirts, posters &amp; more in the same artistic style.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>New Fractal Fruit paintjob &amp; more integrated gravel bikes, too</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Santa Rosa Integrated steel road bike with new Composite Damping System carbon seatmast, in new Fractal Fruit paint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job-297x297.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job-120x120.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_new-Fractal-Fruit-paint-job-768x768.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo by <a href=\"http://instagram.com/william_bender\" target=\"_blank\">Will Bender</a>/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another fresh new Scarab look available across their range is this Fractal Fruit. Get a closer look at that Santa Rosa road bike with the new Composite Damping System. The personal ride of Scarab’s PR manager, the colorful block scheme makes for a bike that will always stand out. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Santa Rosa Integrated steel road bike with new Composite Damping System carbon seatmast, in new Fractal Fruit paint with Wolf Tooth IN-Route headset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Santa-Rosa-Composite-Damping-System-steel-and-carbon-road-bike_photo-by-Will-Bender_integrated-cockpit-up-close-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo by Will Bender/Scarab)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This one features a sleek integrated build with that new low-stack <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-components-enve-in-route-headset/\" target=\"_blank\">Wolf Tooth In-Route</a> internal routing headset that also debuted at MADE. Then, paired to a 1-piece Vision Metron 5D ACR EVO carbon cockpit.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Paramo Integrated gravel bike, cockpit detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike_IN-Route-cockpit-up-close-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Scarab also added the fully integrated cable routing solution to their Paramo Integrated gravel bike, as well. It features the same straight 44mm headtube, with a Wolf Tooth In-Route headset pressed in. Then paired to a carbon Enve In-Route Gravel fork and carbon Enve SES AR 1-piece all-road cockpit. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike.jpg\" alt=\"Scarab Cycles Paramo Integrated gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Scarab-Paramo-Integrated-modern-steel-gravel-bike-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With 48mm tire clearance out back, a UDH, and finally a T47 BB… this integrated frameset starts at $3600 including the fork &amp; headset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://scarabcycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>ScarabCycles.com</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/scarab-carbon-seat-mast-makes-steel-more-comfy-plus-new-andes-road-touring-bike/\">Scarab Carbon Seat Mast Makes Steel More Comfy, Plus New Andes Road Touring Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"483454792dbc6d576d54f4bd2c9cddb5ae129446c6d4e2464ddef9bc3ae0a8c6","category":"Cycling"}